PROBLEM: The current app has a default React Navigation header that 
shows a back arrow + screen title in a top bar. This looks like a 
web app, not a mobile app. Remove or replace it correctly.

RULES:
- Set headerShown: false on ALL stack and tab navigators
- Do NOT use the default navigation header anywhere
- Each screen builds its own top section natively as part of the 
  ScrollView or View content — NOT as a floating nav bar
- For screens that need a back button, use a custom inline header 
  component (see below)
- The status bar should use: 
  <StatusBar barStyle="dark-content" backgroundColor={Colors.bg} />

Custom inline header pattern to use on detail/inner screens:
  <View style={styles.inlineHeader}>
