---

**On the top bar issue** — you're right, it's a common mistake. The default React Navigation header looks like a browser/web pattern. Real mobile apps either hide it entirely and design the greeting/title as part of the screen content (like WhatsApp, Instagram, Grab), or use a very minimal custom one with no background box. The prompt above sets `headerShown: false` everywhere and shows the correct inline back-button pattern for inner screens.